{"questionId":"13496","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Steffi the stray cat often visits Will’s house in search of food. Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span> be the discrete random&nbsp;variable “the number of times per day that Steffi visits Will’s house”.</p>\n<p>The random variable <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span> can be modelled by a Poisson distribution with mean 2.1.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let<em> Y</em> be the discrete random variable “the number of times per day that Steffi is fed at Will’s&nbsp;house”. Steffi is only fed on the first four occasions that she visits each day.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>In any given year of 365 days, the probability that Steffi does not visit Will for at most <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span> days in total is 0.5 (to one decimal place). Find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n</math></span> be the no of days per year that Steffi does not visit</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T \\sim B\\left( {365{\\text{,}}\\,\\,0.122 \\ldots } \\right)\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mo>∼</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>365</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>,</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mn>0.122</mn>\n      <mo>…</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>require&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.45 \\leqslant {\\text{P}}\\left( {T \\leqslant n} \\right) < 0.55\">\n  <mn>0.45</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mo>⩽</mo>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>0.55</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {T \\leqslant 44} \\right) = 0.51\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mo>⩽</mo>\n      <mn>44</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.51</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n = 44\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>44</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13496","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_10d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"In any given year of 365 days, the probability that Steffi does not visit Will for at most n days in total is 0.5 (to one decimal place). Find the value of n .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Properties of discrete and continuous random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}